## Frequently Asked Questions About Equipment Financing Tax Benefits

### 1. What are the main tax benefits of equipment financing in Malaysia?

The main tax benefits include capital allowances (initial allowance of 20% and annual allowance of 14%), interest expense deductions on financing, accelerated capital allowances for certain equipment, and the ability to claim GST/SST input tax credits where applicable.

### 2. What is the difference between initial allowance and annual allowance?

Initial allowance is a one-time deduction of 20% of the equipment's qualifying expenditure claimed in the first year. Annual allowance is 14% of the original cost claimed every year over approximately 7 years until the asset is fully written off.

### 3. Can I claim interest expenses on equipment financing?

Yes, interest expenses incurred on financing used for business purposes are fully tax-deductible under Section 33(1) of the Income Tax Act 1967, provided the equipment is used to generate business income.

### 4. Which is better for tax purposes: hire purchase or leasing?

Hire purchase allows you to claim capital allowances and interest deductions, beneficial for profitable companies. Operating leases allow full rental payment deductions, which can provide better cash flow for companies with lower profits. The choice depends on your company's profitability and cash flow situation.

### 5. What is accelerated capital allowance and who qualifies?

Accelerated capital allowance allows initial allowance up to 100% for specific industries or equipment types. Qualifying categories include environmental protection equipment, automation equipment, ICT equipment, and equipment for specific promoted industries. Check with LHDN or MIDA for current qualifying criteria.

### 6. How do I claim equipment financing tax deductions with LHDN?

Maintain proper documentation including purchase invoices, financing agreements, and payment records. Use Form C (for Sdn Bhd) or Form B (for sole proprietor/partnership) to declare income. Complete Schedule 6 for capital allowance claims and include interest expenses under business expenses. Submit through e-Filing system before the deadline.

### 7. Can SMEs get additional tax incentives for equipment purchases?

Yes, SMEs may qualify for additional incentives including accelerated capital allowances for automation and modernization, special deductions for technology adoption, reinvestment allowances, and industry-specific incentives from MIDA or MITI.

### 8. What records do I need to maintain for tax purposes?

You must maintain equipment purchase invoices and agreements, financing/hire purchase documentation, payment schedules and receipts, depreciation schedules, logbooks for vehicle usage, maintenance records, and insurance documentation. Records must be kept for 7 years as per LHDN requirements.

### 9. Can I claim deductions if my company makes a loss?

Yes, you can still claim capital allowances during loss-making years. These deductions increase your losses, which can be carried forward to offset future profits. There's no time limit for carrying forward business losses in Malaysia.

### 10. What happens if I sell the equipment before fully claiming allowances?

If you sell qualifying plant and machinery before claiming the full annual allowance, you may claim a balancing allowance (if sold at a loss) or may need to declare a balancing charge (if sold at a gain). The treatment depends on the sale price relative to the written-down value.

